Organization Name: COMMUNITY ENRICHMENT CENTER (CEC) | MAIN OFFICE | EMPLOYMENT AND FINANCIAL COACHING
Description: Provides employment and financial coaching. Secondary Services include job search techniques, employment skills, budgeting tools, credit building and more.

Organization Name: GUARDIANSHIP SERVICES (GSI) | MAIN OFFICE | FINANCIAL EXPLOITATION PREVENTION CENTER
Description: Provides education to the public on financial exploitation, prevention and exploitation recovery.

Organization Name: CITY OF FORT WORTH | TARRANT COUNTY COLLEGE - SOUTH CAMPUS | FINANCIAL COACHING WORKSHOP
Description: Provides a workshop on topics like budgeting, banking, borrowing, and credit. Participants are eligible for a $200 dollar-for-dollar savings match after completing four financial coaching sessions.

Organization Name: NAVAL AIR STATION JOINT RESERVE BASE - FORT WORTH | FLEET AND FAMILY SUPPORT CENTER | MILITARY FAMILY SUPPORT SERVICES
Description: Provides transition assistance, financial readiness and money management, job search assistance, parenting skills and life skills classes, food pantry, and family and individual counseling. The Fleet and Family Support Center also serves as a contact point for military families with special needs such as chronic illnesses and/or disabilities through the Exceptional Family Member Program.

Organization Name: FAMILY PATHFINDERS OF TARRANT COUNTY | MAIN OFFICE | FINANCIAL CAPABILITY PROGRAM
Description: Provides financial coaching sessions that include topics such as budgeting, banking, borrowing and credit. Sessions are available in person or virtually in a 45 to 90 minute format. Individual sessions with a financial coach are available upon request. Virtual and in person sessions are available and can be accessed through the Pathfinders website.

Organization Name: MANSFIELD MISSION CENTER | MISSION CENTER | SUPPORTIVE SERVICES
Description: Provides Employment Services include job training and/or certifications for in-demand jobs, employment workshops and assistance with job search, mock interviews, resume writing, and financial coaching. Scholarships for certifications are also available.Offers adults Support with utility, and assistance with application for state benefits such as SNAP, Medicaid, CHIP, and TANF. Note: The agency does not assist with deposit or reconnection or late fees. By making this referral, we know you fit the basic eligibility for this service. However, the referral to this agency is not a guarantee of assistance.
